# Chief Complaint
- Decreased in Judgement
- Confusion
- Nasal Congestion
- Sneezing Fits
- Nasal Discharge
- Cough


# History of Present Illness
Dustin31 is a 77 year-old non-hispanic white male. Patient has a history of acute allergic reaction, concussion with no loss of consciousness, overlapping malignant neoplasm of colon, acute viral pharyngitis (disorder), polyp of colon, viral sinusitis (disorder), fracture of ankle, childhood asthma, acute bronchitis (disorder), laceration of thigh, otitis media, sprain of ankle, first degree burn.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is temporarily homeless. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic. Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a middle socioeconomic background. Patient did not finish high school. Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
latex allergy, allergy to soya

# Medications
acetaminophen 325 mg oral tablet; 120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epinephrine 1 mg/ml injection; atropine sulfate 1 mg/ml injectable solution; prednisone 5 mg oral tablet; 3 ml amiodarone hydrocholoride 50 mg/ml prefilled syringe; aspirin 81 mg oral tablet; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet

# Assessment and Plan
Patient is presenting with fracture subluxation of wrist. 

## Plan

The following procedures were conducted:
- x-ray or wrist
- bone immobilization
- bone density scan (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- meperidine hydrochloride 50 mg oral tablet
- ibuprofen 200 mg oral tablet
The patient was placed on a careplan:
- fracture care
